---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import { localizedPath } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Contact WorthCalc"
  description="Reach the WorthCalc team about calculator bugs, math corrections, feature requests, or partnership inquiries."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-03"
  alternateLocales={['en', 'zh', 'es', 'fr', 'de']}
>
  <p>
    WorthCalc is a small, independently run site, so we keep contact simple:
    email us directly rather than filling out a form.
  </p>
  <p>
    Email: <a href="mailto:btcson66@gmail.com">btcson66@gmail.com</a>
  </p>
  <h2>What to include in a calculator bug report</h2>
  <p>
    Send the exact page URL, every value you entered, the displayed result,
    and the result you expected. Include the currency, time period, decimal
    separator, browser, and device if any of those may matter. A screenshot is
    useful for a layout problem, but please copy the numbers into the email so
    we can reproduce the formula instead of guessing from an image.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>You think a calculator's math is wrong — tell us the inputs you used and what result you expected, and we will check it.</li>
    <li>A default value (like a membership fee or interest rate) looks out of date.</li>
    <li>You have an idea for a new "is it worth it" calculator.</li>
    <li>You found a bug, broken link, or display issue on mobile or desktop.</li>
    <li>You're interested in advertising or a partnership.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Keep personal and financial details out of email</h2>
  <p>
    Do not send passwords, government identification, a full address, card or
    bank-account numbers, a pay stub, or an unredacted contract. A made-up set
    of values with the same mathematical pattern is usually enough to test a
    bug. For a newsletter request, provide only the email address used and the
    action you want us to take.
  </p>

  <h2>Suggesting a useful new calculator</h2>
  <p>
    The strongest proposals describe a repeated money decision, the costs
    people commonly miss, the inputs that should remain editable, a possible
    formula, and a credible public source. We prioritize decisions that can be
    tested with the reader's own numbers. A brand page that only repeats a
    campaign or an unverifiable marketing statistic is not an editorial fit.
  </p>

  <h2>Partnerships, advertising, and press</h2>
  <p>
    Identify your organization, the purpose of the request, any compensation,
    and every relevant commercial relationship. A sponsor cannot buy a
    preferred calculator result, remove a material limitation, or present an
    advertisement as an independent recommendation. Sending a proposal does
    not guarantee a reply, publication, or agreement.
  </p>

  <h2>What this inbox cannot provide</h2>
  <p>
    This address is not personal financial advice, an emergency channel, or a
    bank's customer-support desk. We cannot decide whether you should take a
    loan, buy a home, or make an investment. For suspected fraud, a legal
    deadline, a contract dispute, or immediate danger, contact the appropriate
    authority or qualified professional where you live.
  </p>
  <p>
    We read every message, though as a small team we can't guarantee a
    response to every one. For general questions about how the site works,
    see the <a href={localizedPath(locale, '/about')}>About page</a>, and for
    how we handle data, see our
    <a href={localizedPath(locale, '/privacy')}>Privacy Policy</a>.
    Reproducible math errors and corrections supported by a primary source
    receive priority; material fixes are dated or recorded in the site
    changelog so readers can verify what changed.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
